## Business simulation — newsvendor (GM=35%, full spoilage)

Order placed per (branch,product,day); compared to realised demand on the backtest folds.
Cost = lost margin on stockouts + spoilage on overstock.

| Order policy | total cost (₭) | stockout% | waste% | fill% | avg order |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|

| baseline (moving_avg_7) | 3,706,158,135 | 31.7 | 20.8 | 81.0 | 6.86 |
| LGBM P50 | 2,936,968,955 | 34.2 | 14.8 | 80.0 | 6.30 |
| LGBM P85 | 6,066,010,680 | 10.6 | 33.2 | 93.8 | 9.42 |
| LGBM P95 | 10,068,618,740 | 4.1 | 45.7 | 97.3 | 12.04 |
| LGBM newsvendor (CR=0.35) | 3,048,098,715 | 54.1 | 8.0 | 60.4 | 4.41 |

**Lowest-cost policy: LGBM P50** — ₭2,936,968,955 vs baseline ₭3,706,158,135 → **21% cost cut** over 608,261 order-days.
Note: ₭ cost is on the backtest test window; scales with full network/year.


